{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312040258dee074d3287044e6","session_id":"da6f98d4-7e33-4c58-9c42-a371874e10ea","message":{"id":"20260312040258dee074d3287044e6","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde7edbc3829383044130a00d2a74","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/pipeline-controller.js"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":24740,"output_tokens":150,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_25d15181ab0046938b2fac6f","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:03:02.177Z","_requestId":"2a50dd388a364b15840cdcad9dcd8a24"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"0e0291e5-d249-410f-bbbf-e57007fb1f3a","session_id":"da6f98d4-7e33-4c58-9c42-a371874e10ea","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde7ed858530ffaca6f6c15cb3132","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→构建 pipeline 进程控制层，统一封装 dev-pipeline/run.sh 与 run-bugfix.sh 的启动、停止、重试、单特性执行与后台守护模式。该层提供稳定 API 给 Telegram 命令路由调用，并负责并发锁、超时、退出码映射与异常恢复。目标是把当前\"终端操作脚本\"能力抽象为\"程序可调用控制接口\"。\n   6→\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→## User Stories\n  10→\n  11→### US-1: Unified Pipeline Start\n  12→\n  13→**As a** Telegram 用户或系统集成者  \n  14→**I want** 通过统一的控制接口启动 feature pipeline 或 bugfix pipeline  \n  15→**So that** 我不需要关心底层脚本的差异，且能获得标准化的执行结果\n  16→\n  17→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  18→- AC-1.1: `startPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix', targetId?, listPath?, daemon?: boolean })` 可启动指定类型管道\n  19→- AC-1.2: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, runId, pid?, message, errorCode? }`\n  20→- AC-1.3: 若指定 `daemon: true`，以后台守护模式启动，返回 PID\n  21→- AC-1.4: 若管道已在运行中（并发锁检查失败），返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误\n  22→\n  23→---\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: Pipeline Stop\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 运维人员  \n  28→**I want** 通过控制接口停止正在运行的管道  \n  29→**So that** 我可以从 Telegram 或 API 中止异常的管道执行\n  30→\n  31→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  32→- AC-2.1: `stopPipeline({ type: 'feature' | 'bugfix' })` 可停止指定类型的守护进程\n  33→- AC-2.2: 若进程已停止，返回 `ALREADY_STOPPED` 状态而非错误\n  34→- AC-2.3: 停止操作有 10 秒超时，超时后强制终止\n  35→- AC-2.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, previousPid, message }`\n  36→\n  37→---\n  38→\n  39→### US-3: Target Retry\n  40→\n  41→**As a** 开发者  \n  42→**I want** 重试某个失败的 feature 或 bugfix 目标  \n  43→**So that** 我可以针对单个失败项进行修复而不影响其他已完成的工作\n  44→\n  45→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  46→- AC-3.1: `retryTarget({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可重试指定目标\n  47→- AC-3.2: 若目标不存在或状态不允许可重试，返回明确错误\n  48→- AC-3.3: 支持前台和后台模式\n  49→- AC-3.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, targetId, message }`\n  50→\n  51→---\n  52→\n  53→### US-4: Run Single Feature\n  54→\n  55→**As a** 开发者  \n  56→**I want** 单独运行某个特定的 feature 或 bugfix  \n  57→**So that** 我可以测试或调试单个工作项而不运行整个队列\n  58→\n  59→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  60→- AC-4.1: `runSingle({ type, targetId, listPath? })` 可执行单个目标\n  61→- AC-4.2: 执行完成后返回完整的执行结果（含 stdout/stderr）\n  62→- AC-4.3: 支持超时配置\n  63→- AC-4.4: 不影响管道整体状态（独立执行）\n  64→\n  65→---\n  66→\n  67→### US-5: Status Query\n  68→\n  69→**As a** 运维人员  \n  70→**I want** 查询管道的当前状态  \n  71→**So that** 我可以了解系统运行情况并做出决策\n  72→\n  73→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  74→- AC-5.1: `getPipelineStatus({ type })` 返回管道状态对象\n  75→- AC-5.2: 状态对象包含 `{ isRunning, pid?, currentFeature?, startedAt?, lastResult? }`\n  76→- AC-5.3: 若有运行中的目标，包含 `currentFeature` 和 `startedAt`\n  77→- AC-5.4: 若无运行中管道，返回 `lastResult`（最近一次执行结果）\n  78→\n  79→---\n  80→\n  81→### US-6: Logs Query\n  82→\n  83→**As a** 运维人员  \n  84→**I want** 获取管道执行日志  \n  85→**So that** 我可以诊断问题或监控执行进度\n  86→\n  87→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  88→- AC-6.1: `getPipelineLogs({ type, lines?: number })` 返回日志内容\n  89→- AC-6.2: 默认返回最近 100 行，可通过 `lines` 参数调整\n  90→- AC-6.3: 日志不存在时返回空字符串而非错误\n  91→- AC-6.4: 返回结构化结果 `{ ok, logs, logPath }`\n  92→\n  93→---\n  94→\n  95→### US-7: Concurrency Protection\n  96→\n  97→**As a** 系统管理员  \n  98→**I want** 防止多个管道实例同时运行  \n  99→**So that** 系统资源不被过度占用且状态文件不会冲突\n 100→\n 101→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 102→- AC-7.1: 同类型管道同一时间只能有一个实例运行\n 103→- AC-7.2: 锁获取失败时返回 `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED` 错误，含当前持有者信息\n 104→- AC-7.3: 锁在进程异常退出时自动释放（通过 PID 检测）\n 105→- AC-7.4: 提供 `forceUnlock({ type })` 用于强制释放锁（管理员操作）\n 106→\n 107→---\n 108→\n 109→### US-8: Error Mapping\n 110→\n 111→**As a** Telegram handler 开发者  \n 112→**I want** 所有错误都有结构化的错误码和消息  \n 113→**So that** 我可以向用户展示友好的错误提示而非原始错误堆栈\n 114→\n 115→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 116→- AC-8.1: 所有错误返回 `{ ok: false, errorCode: string, message: string, hint?: string }`\n 117→- AC-8.2: 错误码覆盖: `LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED`, `SCRIPT_NOT_FOUND`, `EXEC_TIMEOUT`, `EXEC_FAILED`, `INVALID_TARGET`, `PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING`, `ALREADY_STOPPED`\n 118→- AC-8.3: 超时错误包含超时时长信息\n 119→- AC-8.4: 脚本缺失错误包含脚本路径\n 120→\n 121→---\n 122→\n 123→### US-9: Telegram Handler Integration\n 124→\n 125→**As a** Telegram bot 开发者  \n 126→**I want** 控制层接口可直接被 Telegram handler 调用  \n 127→**So that** 命令路由实现变得简单且不依赖终端交互\n 128→\n 129→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n 130→- AC-9.1: 所有方法返回 Promise，可被 async/await 调用\n 131→- AC-9.2: 无需传递 process.stdin/stdout 依赖\n 132→- AC-9.3: 执行结果可通过 JSON 序列化传输\n 133→- AC-9.4: 提供 `createPipelineController()` 工厂函数，支持依赖注入\n 134→\n 135→---\n 136→\n 137→## Non-Functional Requirements\n 138→\n 139→### NFR-1: Performance\n 140→- 控制接口响应时间 < 100ms（不含脚本执行时间）\n 141→- 状态查询 < 50ms\n 142→- 日志读取（100 行）< 200ms\n 143→\n 144→### NFR-2: Reliability\n 145→- 锁机制可靠性 > 99.9%（无死锁场景）\n 146→- 进程异常退出时资源清理率 100%\n 147→\n 148→### NFR-3: Maintainability\n 149→- 核心模块单文件，函数长度 < 100 行\n 150→- 错误码定义在单一文件中管理\n 151→- 测试覆盖率 > 90%\n 152→\n 153→### NFR-4: Extensibility\n 154→- 支持未来添加新的 pipeline 类型（如 `planner`）\n 155→- 错误码可扩展\n 156→- 状态模型可扩展\n 157→\n 158→---\n 159→\n 160→## Scope Boundaries\n 161→\n 162→### In Scope\n 163→- Pipeline 控制器核心模块 (`src/services/process-controller.js`)\n 164→- 并发锁管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js`)\n 165→- 状态管理器 (`src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js`)\n 166→- 错误码扩展 (`src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js`)\n 167→- 与现有 daemon 脚本的集成\n 168→- 单元测试与集成测试\n 169→\n 170→### Out of Scope\n 171→- Telegram 命令路由实现（已在 F-002 完成）\n 172→- Pipeline 内部逻辑修改\n 173→- Web UI\n 174→- 数据库持久化（继续使用 JSON 文件）\n 175→- 认证授权（由上层路由处理）\n 176→\n 177→---\n 178→\n 179→## Dependencies\n 180→\n 181→| Dependency | Type | Status | Notes |\n 182→|------------|------|--------|-------|\n 183→| F-001 | Feature | completed | 提供基础架构 (script-runner, error-codes, path-policy) |\n 184→| F-002 | Feature | completed | 提供命令路由层 (将调用 F-004 API) |\n 185→| launch-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Feature daemon 管理脚本 |\n 186→| launch-bugfix-daemon.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix daemon 管理脚本 |\n 187→| retry-feature.sh | Script | existing | Feature 重试脚本 |\n 188→| retry-bug.sh | Script | existing | Bugfix 重试脚本 |\n 189→\n 190→---\n 191→\n 192→## Risks\n 193→\n 194→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 195→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 196→| 并发锁实现复杂导致死锁 | Medium | High | 使用简单的文件锁 + PID 检测，避免复杂同步原语 |\n 197→| Daemon 脚本输出格式变化 | Low | Medium | 建立脚本输出契约，添加输出解析测试 |\n 198→| 大日志文件读取阻塞 | Low | Medium | 使用流式读取或限制读取行数 |\n 199→| 跨平台兼容性（macOS/Linux） | Low | Low | 主要使用 Node.js API，脚本在 WSL/Git Bash 兼容 |\n 200→\n 201→---\n 202→\n 203→## Technical Notes\n 204→\n 205→### 现有基础设施\n 206→- `script-runner.js` 已提供基本的命令执行和错误映射\n 207→- `pipeline-control-service.js` 已提供基础 API，但缺少并发保护和 daemon 模式\n 208→- `launch-daemon.sh` 和 `launch-bugfix-daemon.sh` 提供 PID 管理和日志合并\n 209→\n 210→### 设计方向\n 211→- 扩展 `pipeline-control-service.js` 或创建新模块 `process-controller.js`\n 212→- 锁管理器使用文件锁 (`flock` 或 `.lock` 文件 + PID 校验)\n 213→- 状态管理器读取现有的 `pipeline.json` 和 `.pipeline-meta.json`\n 214→\n 215→---\n 216→\n 217→## Decisions\n 218→\n 219→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 220→|----|------|----------|\n 221→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用文件锁 + PID 校验实现并发保护，避免引入外部依赖 |\n 222→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 创建独立的 `process-controller.js` 模块，而非扩展现有 `pipeline-control-service.js`，以保持职责清晰 |\n 223→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 复用现有 daemon 脚本的输出格式，不做脚本修改 |\n 224→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_25d15181ab0046938b2fac6f","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:03:02.189Z","_requestId":"2a50dd388a364b15840cdcad9dcd8a24"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"df51691d-6fbc-43b1-a5c6-505e3cfdf07b","session_id":"da6f98d4-7e33-4c58-9c42-a371874e10ea","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde7eda480dcfe786540b1175e43d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→/**\n   2→ * State Manager\n   3→ *\n   4→ * F-004: Pipeline Process Controller - US-5 Status Query, US-6 Logs Query\n   5→ *\n   6→ * Manages reading and writing pipeline state files including:\n   7→ * - Daemon meta (.pipeline-meta.json)\n   8→ * - Pipeline state (pipeline.json)\n   9→ * - Current session (current-session.json)\n  10→ * - Last result (.last-result.json)\n  11→ *\n  12→ * Design Decisions:\n  13→ * - D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n  14→ * - D6: Last result stored in separate file\n  15→ */\n  16→\n  17→import fs from 'node:fs';\n  18→import path from 'node:path';\n  19→\n  20→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './config-loader.js';\n  21→import { getStatePaths } from './path-policy.js';\n  22→\n  23→/**\n  24→ * @typedef {'feature' | 'bugfix'} PipelineType\n  25→ */\n  26→\n  27→/**\n  28→ * @typedef {Object} DaemonMeta\n  29→ * @property {number} pid - Daemon process ID\n  30→ * @property {string} started_at - ISO timestamp when daemon started\n  31→ * @property {string} feature_list - Path to feature list\n  32→ * @property {string} env_overrides - Environment overrides string\n  33→ * @property {string} log_file - Path to log file\n  34→ */\n  35→\n  36→/**\n  37→ * @typedef {Object} PipelineState\n  38→ * @property {string} run_id - Unique run identifier\n  39→ * @property {string} status - Pipeline status (running/paused/completed/failed)\n  40→ * @property {string} feature_list_path - Path to feature list\n  41→ * @property {string} created_at - ISO timestamp when created\n  42→ * @property {number} total_features - Total features to process\n  43→ * @property {number} completed_features - Number of completed features\n  44→ * @property {string} [paused_at] - ISO timestamp when paused\n  45→ */\n  46→\n  47→/**\n  48→ * @typedef {Object} LastResult\n  49→ * @property {string} runId - Run identifier\n  50→ * @property {string} completedAt - ISO timestamp when completed\n  51→ * @property {'success' | 'failed' | 'partial'} status - Completion status\n  52→ * @property {number} featuresTotal - Total features\n  53→ * @property {number} featuresCompleted - Completed features count\n  54→ * @property {number} [exitCode] - Exit code\n  55→ * @property {string} [message] - Result message\n  56→ */\n  57→\n  58→/**\n  59→ * Safely read and parse a JSON file.\n  60→ * @param {string} filePath - File path\n  61→ * @returns {Object | null} Parsed JSON or null if file doesn't exist\n  62→ */\n  63→function readJsonFile(filePath) {\n  64→  try {\n  65→    const content = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n  66→    return JSON.parse(content);\n  67→  } catch {\n  68→    return null;\n  69→  }\n  70→}\n  71→\n  72→/**\n  73→ * Write JSON to file atomically.\n  74→ * @param {string} filePath - File path\n  75→ * @param {Object} data - Data to write\n  76→ */\n  77→function writeJsonFile(filePath, data) {\n  78→  const dir = path.dirname(filePath);\n  79→  if (!fs.existsSync(dir)) {\n  80→    fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n  81→  }\n  82→\n  83→  const tempPath = `${filePath}.${Date.now()}.tmp`;\n  84→  fs.writeFileSync(tempPath, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n  85→  fs.renameSync(tempPath, filePath);\n  86→}\n  87→\n  88→/**\n  89→ * Check if a process is alive.\n  90→ * @param {number} pid - Process ID to check\n  91→ * @returns {boolean} True if process is alive\n  92→ */\n  93→function isProcessAlive(pid) {\n  94→  try {\n  95→    process.kill(pid, 0);\n  96→    return true;\n  97→  } catch (error) {\n  98→    return error.code !== 'ESRCH';\n  99→  }\n 100→}\n 101→\n 102→/**\n 103→ * Create a state manager instance.\n 104→ * @param {Object} [options] - Options\n 105→ * @param {Object} [options.config] - Pipeline config (will load if not provided)\n 106→ * @returns {Object} State manager instance\n 107→ */\n 108→export function createStateManager(options = {}) {\n 109→  const config = options.config ?? loadPipelineInfraConfig();\n 110→\n 111→  /**\n 112→   * Get state paths for pipeline type.\n 113→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 114→   * @returns {Object} State paths\n 115→   */\n 116→  function getPaths(type) {\n 117→    return getStatePaths(config.projectRoot, type);\n 118→  }\n 119→\n 120→  /**\n 121→   * Read daemon meta file.\n 122→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 123→   * @returns {Promise<DaemonMeta | null>} Daemon meta or null\n 124→   */\n 125→  async function readDaemonMeta(type) {\n 126→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 127→    return readJsonFile(paths.daemonMetaFile);\n 128→  }\n 129→\n 130→  /**\n 131→   * Read pipeline state file.\n 132→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 133→   * @returns {Promise<PipelineState | null>} Pipeline state or null\n 134→   */\n 135→  async function readPipelineState(type) {\n 136→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 137→    return readJsonFile(paths.pipelineStateFile);\n 138→  }\n 139→\n 140→  /**\n 141→   * Read current session file.\n 142→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 143→   * @returns {Promise<Object | null>} Current session or null\n 144→   */\n 145→  async function readCurrentSession(type) {\n 146→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 147→    return readJsonFile(paths.currentSessionFile);\n 148→  }\n 149→\n 150→  /**\n 151→   * Get last result.\n 152→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 153→   * @returns {Promise<LastResult | null>} Last result or null\n 154→   */\n 155→  async function getLastResult(type) {\n 156→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 157→    return readJsonFile(paths.lastResultFile);\n 158→  }\n 159→\n 160→  /**\n 161→   * Write daemon meta file.\n 162→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 163→   * @param {DaemonMeta} meta - Daemon meta to write\n 164→   * @returns {Promise<void>}\n 165→   */\n 166→  async function writeDaemonMeta(type, meta) {\n 167→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 168→    writeJsonFile(paths.daemonMetaFile, meta);\n 169→  }\n 170→\n 171→  /**\n 172→   * Write last result file.\n 173→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 174→   * @param {LastResult} result - Last result to write\n 175→   * @returns {Promise<void>}\n 176→   */\n 177→  async function writeLastResult(type, result) {\n 178→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 179→    writeJsonFile(paths.lastResultFile, result);\n 180→  }\n 181→\n 182→  /**\n 183→   * Check if daemon is running.\n 184→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 185→   * @returns {Promise<boolean>} True if daemon is running\n 186→   */\n 187→  async function isDaemonRunning(type) {\n 188→    const meta = await readDaemonMeta(type);\n 189→    if (!meta || !meta.pid) {\n 190→      return false;\n 191→    }\n 192→    return isProcessAlive(meta.pid);\n 193→  }\n 194→\n 195→  /**\n 196→   * Get daemon PID.\n 197→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 198→   * @returns {Promise<number | null>} Daemon PID or null\n 199→   */\n 200→  async function getDaemonPid(type) {\n 201→    const meta = await readDaemonMeta(type);\n 202→    return meta?.pid ?? null;\n 203→  }\n 204→\n 205→  /**\n 206→   * Read log file with line limit.\n 207→   * @param {PipelineType} type - Pipeline type\n 208→   * @param {number} [lines] - Number of lines (default: 100)\n 209→   * @returns {Promise<{logs: string, logPath: string, lines: number}>}\n 210→   */\n 211→  async function readLogs(type, lines = 100) {\n 212→    const paths = getPaths(type);\n 213→    const logPath = paths.daemonLogFile;\n 214→\n 215→    if (!fs.existsSync(logPath)) {\n 216→      return { logs: '', logPath, lines: 0 };\n 217→    }\n 218→\n 219→    try {\n 220→      const content = fs.readFileSync(logPath, 'utf8');\n 221→      const allLines = content.split('\\n');\n 222→      const selectedLines = allLines.slice(-lines);\n 223→      return {\n 224→        logs: selectedLines.join('\\n'),\n 225→        logPath,\n 226→        lines: selectedLines.filter(l => l.trim()).length\n 227→      };\n 228→    } catch {\n 229→      return { logs: '', logPath, lines: 0 };\n 230→    }\n 231→  }\n 232→\n 233→  return {\n 234→    readDaemonMeta,\n 235→    readPipelineState,\n 236→    readCurrentSession,\n 237→    getLastResult,\n 238→    writeDaemonMeta,\n 239→    writeLastResult,\n 240→    isDaemonRunning,\n 241→    getDaemonPid,\n 242→    readLogs\n 243→  };\n 244→}\n 245→\n 246→// Default instance\n 247→let defaultManager = null;\n 248→\n 249→/**\n 250→ * Get default state manager instance.\n 251→ * @returns {Object} Default state manager\n 252→ */\n 253→export function getDefaultStateManager() {\n 254→  if (!defaultManager) {\n 255→    defaultManager = createStateManager();\n 256→  }\n 257→  return defaultManager;\n 258→}\n 259→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_25d15181ab0046938b2fac6f","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:03:02.190Z","_requestId":"2a50dd388a364b15840cdcad9dcd8a24"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"299f8f0a-9002-4229-9a66-a70c9156522f","session_id":"da6f98d4-7e33-4c58-9c42-a371874e10ea","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde7edbc3829383044130a00d2a74","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→import fs from 'node:fs';\n   2→import { createLockManager, getDefaultLockManager } from '../pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js';\n   3→import { createStateManager, getDefaultStateManager } from '../pipeline-infra/state-manager.js';\n   4→import { executePipelineCommand, buildPipelineCommand } from '../pipeline-infra/script-runner.js';\n   5→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from '../pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n   6→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from '../pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n   7→import { INFRA_ERROR_CODES } from '../pipeline-infra/error-codes.js';\n   8→\n   9→const DEFAULT_LOG_LINES = 100;\n  10→const DEFAULT_STOP_TIMEOUT_MS = 10000;\n  11→\n  12→/**\n  13→ * Build an error result object.\n  14→ * @param {string} errorCode - Error code\n  15→ * @param {string} message - Error message\n  16→ * @param {Object} [options] - Additional options\n  17→ * @param {string} [options.hint] - Hint for resolving the error\n  18→ * @param {Object} [options.context] - Additional context\n  19→ * @returns {Object} Error result\n  20→ */\n  21→function buildError(errorCode, message, options = {}) {\n  22→  return {\n  23→    ok: false,\n  24→    errorCode,\n  25→    message,\n  26→    ...(options.hint ? { hint: options.hint } : {}),\n  27→    ...(options.context ? { context: options.context } : {})\n  28→  };\n  29→}\n  30→\n  31→/**\n  32→ * Build a success result object.\n  33→ * @param {string} message - Success message\n  34→ * @param {Object} [extra] - Additional fields\n  35→ * @returns {Object} Success result\n  36→ */\n  37→function buildResult(message, extra = {}) {\n  38→  return {\n  39→    ok: true,\n  40→    message,\n  41→    ...extra\n  42→  };\n  43→}\n  44→\n  45→/**\n  46→ * Generate a unique run ID.\n  47→ * @returns {string} Run ID\n  48→ */\n  49→function generateRunId() {\n  50→  const now = new Date();\n  51→  const timestamp = now.toISOString().replace(/[-:T]/g, '').slice(0, 15);\n  52→  return `run-${timestamp}`;\n  53→}\n  54→\n  55→/**\n  56→ * Read last N lines from a file.\n  57→ * @param {string} filePath - Path to file\n  58→ * @param {number} lines - Number of lines to read\n  59→ * @returns {string} File content\n  60→ */\n  61→function readLastLines(filePath, lines) {\n  62→  try {\n  63→    const content = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n  64→    const allLines = content.split('\\n');\n  65→    const selectedLines = allLines.slice(-lines);\n  66→    return selectedLines.join('\\n');\n  67→  } catch {\n  68→    return '';\n  69→  }\n  70→}\n  71→\n  72→/**\n  73→ * Create a pipeline controller instance.\n  74→ * @param {Object} options - Options\n  75→ * @param {Object} [options.lockManager] - Lock manager instance\n  76→ * @param {Object} [options.stateManager] - State manager instance\n  77→ * @param {Function} [options.scriptRunner] - Script runner function\n  78→ * @param {Object} [options.config] - Pipeline config\n  79→ * @returns {Object} Pipeline controller interface\n  80→ */\n  81→export function createPipelineController(options = {}) {\n  82→  const lockManager = options.lockManager || getDefaultLockManager();\n  83→  const stateManager = options.stateManager || getDefaultStateManager();\n  84→  const scriptRunner = options.scriptRunner || executePipelineCommand;\n  85→  const config = options.config || loadPipelineInfraConfig();\n  86→\n  87→  /**\n  88→   * Internal: Acquire lock and return result.\n  89→   * @param {string} type - Pipeline type\n  90→   * @returns {Promise<Object|null>} Lock result or null on success\n  91→   */\n  92→  async function _acquireLock(type) {\n  93→    const lockResult = await lockManager.acquireLock(type);\n  94→    if (!lockResult.ok) {\n  95→      return buildError(\n  96→        INFRA_ERROR_CODES.LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED,\n  97→        `Pipeline ${type} is already running`,\n  98→        {\n  99→          hint: 'Stop the current pipeline first or use forceUnlock',\n 100→          context: { currentHolder: lockResult.currentHolder }\n 101→        }\n 102→      );\n 103→    }\n 104→    return null;\n 105→  }\n 106→\n 107→  /**\n 108→   * Internal: Release lock.\n 109→   * @param {string} type - Pipeline type\n 110→   */\n 111→  async function _releaseLock(type) {\n 112→    await lockManager.releaseLock(type);\n 113→  }\n 114→\n 115→  return {\n 116→    // Internal methods (exposed for testing)\n 117→    _acquireLock,\n 118→    _releaseLock,\n 119→\n 120→    /**\n 121→     * Start a pipeline.\n 122→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 123→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 124→     * @param {string} [params.targetId] - Optional target ID to start with\n 125→     * @param {string} [params.listPath] - Optional list path\n 126→     * @param {boolean} [params.daemon=true] - Run in daemon mode\n 127→     * @param {Object} [params.envOverrides] - Environment overrides\n 128→     * @param {number} [params.timeoutMs] - Timeout in milliseconds\n 129→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Start result\n 130→     */\n 131→    async startPipeline(params) {\n 132→      const { type = 'feature', targetId, listPath, daemon = true, envOverrides, timeoutMs } = params;\n 133→\n 134→      // Acquire lock\n 135→      const lockError = await _acquireLock(type);\n 136→      if (lockError) {\n 137→        return lockError;\n 138→      }\n 139→\n 140→      // Build and execute command\n 141→      const runId = generateRunId();\n 142→\n 143→      try {\n 144→        const result = await scriptRunner({\n 145→          pipelineType: type,\n 146→          action: 'run',\n 147→          targetId,\n 148→          listPath,\n 149→          envOverrides,\n 150→          timeoutMs\n 151→        });\n 152→\n 153→        if (!result.ok) {\n 154→          // Release lock on failure\n 155→          await _releaseLock(type);\n 156→          return buildError(\n 157→            result.errorCode || INFRA_ERROR_CODES.DAEMON_START_FAILED,\n 158→            result.stderr || 'Failed to start pipeline',\n 159→            { context: { exitCode: result.exitCode } }\n 160→          );\n 161→        }\n 162→\n 163→        return buildResult(`Pipeline ${type} started successfully`, {\n 164→          runId,\n 165→          pid: daemon ? process.pid : undefined,\n 166→          stdout: result.stdout\n 167→        });\n 168→      } catch (error) {\n 169→        await _releaseLock(type);\n 170→        return buildError(\n 171→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.DAEMON_START_FAILED,\n 172→          error.message,\n 173→          { hint: 'Check pipeline scripts and configuration' }\n 174→        );\n 175→      }\n 176→    },\n 177→\n 178→    /**\n 179→     * Stop a pipeline.\n 180→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 181→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 182→     * @param {number} [params.timeoutMs=10000] - Timeout in milliseconds\n 183→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Stop result\n 184→     */\n 185→    async stopPipeline(params) {\n 186→      const { type = 'feature', timeoutMs = DEFAULT_STOP_TIMEOUT_MS } = params;\n 187→\n 188→      // Check if daemon is running\n 189→      const isRunning = await stateManager.isDaemonRunning(type);\n 190→      const previousPid = await stateManager.getDaemonPid(type);\n 191→\n 192→      if (!isRunning) {\n 193→        // Already stopped\n 194→        return buildResult(`Pipeline ${type} is not running`, {\n 195→          errorCode: INFRA_ERROR_CODES.ALREADY_STOPPED,\n 196→          previousPid\n 197→        });\n 198→      }\n 199→\n 200→      try {\n 201→        // Execute stop command\n 202→        const result = await scriptRunner({\n 203→          pipelineType: type,\n 204→          action: 'stop',\n 205→          timeoutMs\n 206→        });\n 207→\n 208→        // Release lock\n 209→        await _releaseLock(type);\n 210→\n 211→        if (!result.ok) {\n 212→          return buildError(\n 213→            result.errorCode || INFRA_ERROR_CODES.EXEC_FAILED,\n 214→            result.stderr || 'Failed to stop pipeline',\n 215→            { context: { previousPid } }\n 216→          );\n 217→        }\n 218→\n 219→        return buildResult(`Pipeline ${type} stopped successfully`, {\n 220→          previousPid\n 221→        });\n 222→      } catch (error) {\n 223→        // Still release lock on error\n 224→        await _releaseLock(type);\n 225→        return buildError(\n 226→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.EXEC_FAILED,\n 227→          error.message,\n 228→          { context: { previousPid } }\n 229→        );\n 230→      }\n 231→    },\n 232→\n 233→    /**\n 234→     * Retry a target.\n 235→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 236→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 237→     * @param {string} params.targetId - Target ID to retry\n 238→     * @param {string} [params.listPath] - Optional list path\n 239→     * @param {boolean} [params.daemon=false] - Run in daemon mode\n 240→     * @param {Object} [params.envOverrides] - Environment overrides\n 241→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Retry result\n 242→     */\n 243→    async retryTarget(params) {\n 244→      const { type = 'feature', targetId, listPath, daemon = false, envOverrides } = params;\n 245→\n 246→      // Validate targetId\n 247→      if (!targetId || typeof targetId !== 'string' || targetId.trim() === '') {\n 248→        return buildError(\n 249→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.INVALID_TARGET,\n 250→          'targetId is required for retry',\n 251→          { hint: 'Provide a valid target ID (e.g., F-001 or B-001)' }\n 252→        );\n 253→      }\n 254→\n 255→      // For daemon mode, acquire lock\n 256→      if (daemon) {\n 257→        const lockError = await _acquireLock(type);\n 258→        if (lockError) {\n 259→          return lockError;\n 260→        }\n 261→      }\n 262→\n 263→      try {\n 264→        const result = await scriptRunner({\n 265→          pipelineType: type,\n 266→          action: 'retry',\n 267→          targetId: targetId.trim(),\n 268→          listPath,\n 269→          envOverrides\n 270→        });\n 271→\n 272→        if (daemon) {\n 273→          await _releaseLock(type);\n 274→        }\n 275→\n 276→        if (!result.ok) {\n 277→          return buildError(\n 278→            result.errorCode || INFRA_ERROR_CODES.EXEC_FAILED,\n 279→            result.stderr || `Failed to retry target ${targetId}`,\n 280→            { context: { targetId } }\n 281→          );\n 282→        }\n 283→\n 284→        return buildResult(`Target ${targetId} retry completed`, {\n 285→          targetId,\n 286→          stdout: result.stdout\n 287→        });\n 288→      } catch (error) {\n 289→        if (daemon) {\n 290→          await _releaseLock(type);\n 291→        }\n 292→        return buildError(\n 293→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.EXEC_FAILED,\n 294→          error.message,\n 295→          { context: { targetId } }\n 296→        );\n 297→      }\n 298→    },\n 299→\n 300→    /**\n 301→     * Run a single target without affecting pipeline state.\n 302→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 303→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 304→     * @param {string} params.targetId - Target ID to run\n 305→     * @param {string} [params.listPath] - Optional list path\n 306→     * @param {number} [params.timeoutMs] - Timeout in milliseconds\n 307→     * @param {Object} [params.envOverrides] - Environment overrides\n 308→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Run result\n 309→     */\n 310→    async runSingle(params) {\n 311→      const { type = 'feature', targetId, listPath, timeoutMs, envOverrides } = params;\n 312→\n 313→      // Validate targetId\n 314→      if (!targetId || typeof targetId !== 'string' || targetId.trim() === '') {\n 315→        return buildError(\n 316→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.INVALID_TARGET,\n 317→          'targetId is required for runSingle',\n 318→          { hint: 'Provide a valid target ID (e.g., F-001 or B-001)' }\n 319→        );\n 320→      }\n 321→\n 322→      // Note: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution per D5)\n 323→\n 324→      try {\n 325→        const result = await scriptRunner({\n 326→          pipelineType: type,\n 327→          action: 'run',\n 328→          targetId: targetId.trim(),\n 329→          listPath,\n 330→          timeoutMs,\n 331→          envOverrides\n 332→        });\n 333→\n 334→        return {\n 335→          ok: result.ok,\n 336→          targetId,\n 337→          message: result.ok\n 338→            ? `Target ${targetId} completed successfully`\n 339→            : `Target ${targetId} failed`,\n 340→          stdout: result.stdout,\n 341→          stderr: result.stderr,\n 342→          exitCode: result.exitCode,\n 343→          errorCode: result.errorCode\n 344→        };\n 345→      } catch (error) {\n 346→        return buildError(\n 347→          INFRA_ERROR_CODES.EXEC_FAILED,\n 348→          error.message,\n 349→          { context: { targetId } }\n 350→        );\n 351→      }\n 352→    },\n 353→\n 354→    /**\n 355→     * Get pipeline status.\n 356→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 357→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 358→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Status result\n 359→     */\n 360→    async getStatus(params) {\n 361→      const { type = 'feature' } = params;\n 362→\n 363→      const isRunning = await stateManager.isDaemonRunning(type);\n 364→      const pid = await stateManager.getDaemonPid(type);\n 365→      const pipelineState = await stateManager.readPipelineState(type);\n 366→      const currentSession = await stateManager.readCurrentSession(type);\n 367→      const lastResult = await stateManager.getLastResult(type);\n 368→      const lockInfo = await lockManager.getLockInfo(type);\n 369→\n 370→      const result = {\n 371→        ok: true,\n 372→        isRunning,\n 373→        pid: isRunning ? pid : undefined,\n 374→        message: isRunning\n 375→          ? `Pipeline ${type} is running`\n 376→          : `Pipeline ${type} is not running`\n 377→      };\n 378→\n 379→      // Add current feature info if running\n 380→      if (isRunning && currentSession) {\n 381→        result.currentFeature = currentSession.feature_id;\n 382→        result.startedAt = currentSession.started_at;\n 383→      }\n 384→\n 385→      // Add last result if not running\n 386→      if (!isRunning && lastResult) {\n 387→        result.lastResult = lastResult;\n 388→      }\n 389→\n 390→      // Add lock info\n 391→      if (lockInfo) {\n 392→        result.lockInfo = lockInfo;\n 393→      }\n 394→\n 395→      return result;\n 396→    },\n 397→\n 398→    /**\n 399→     * Get pipeline logs.\n 400→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 401→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 402→     * @param {number} [params.lines=100] - Number of lines to read\n 403→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Logs result\n 404→     */\n 405→    async getLogs(params) {\n 406→      const { type = 'feature', lines = DEFAULT_LOG_LINES } = params;\n 407→\n 408→      const logPaths = resolveDaemonLogPaths(config.projectRoot);\n 409→      const logPath = type === 'feature'\n 410→        ? logPaths.featureDaemonLog\n 411→        : logPaths.bugfixDaemonLog;\n 412→\n 413→      const logs = readLastLines(logPath, lines);\n 414→\n 415→      return buildResult(`Retrieved ${lines} lines from ${type} log`, {\n 416→        logs,\n 417→        logPath,\n 418→        lines\n 419→      });\n 420→    },\n 421→\n 422→    /**\n 423→     * Force unlock a pipeline (admin operation).\n 424→     * @param {Object} params - Parameters\n 425→     * @param {string} params.type - Pipeline type ('feature' or 'bugfix')\n 426→     * @returns {Promise<Object>} Unlock result\n 427→     */\n 428→    async forceUnlock(params) {\n 429→      const { type = 'feature' } = params;\n 430→\n 431→      const result = await lockManager.forceUnlock(type);\n 432→\n 433→      return buildResult(`Lock released for ${type} pipeline`, {\n 434→        previousPid: result.previousPid\n 435→      });\n 436→    }\n 437→  };\n 438→}\n 439→\n 440→// Default instance\n 441→let defaultController = null;\n 442→\n 443→/**\n 444→ * Get the default pipeline controller instance.\n 445→ * @returns {Object} Pipeline controller instance\n 446→ */\n 447→export function getDefaultPipelineController() {\n 448→  if (!defaultController) {\n 449→    defaultController = createPipelineController();\n 450→  }\n 451→  return defaultController;\n 452→}\n 453→\n 454→// Export convenience methods that use default controller\n 455→export async function startPipeline(params) {\n 456→  return getDefaultPipelineController().startPipeline(params);\n 457→}\n 458→\n 459→export async function stopPipeline(params) {\n 460→  return getDefaultPipelineController().stopPipeline(params);\n 461→}\n 462→\n 463→export async function retryTarget(params) {\n 464→  return getDefaultPipelineController().retryTarget(params);\n 465→}\n 466→\n 467→export async function runSingle(params) {\n 468→  return getDefaultPipelineController().runSingle(params);\n 469→}\n 470→\n 471→export async function getStatus(params) {\n 472→  return getDefaultPipelineController().getStatus(params);\n 473→}\n 474→\n 475→export async function getLogs(params) {\n 476→  return getDefaultPipelineController().getLogs(params);\n 477→}\n 478→\n 479→export async function forceUnlock(params) {\n 480→  return getDefaultPipelineController().forceUnlock(params);\n 481→}\n 482→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_25d15181ab0046938b2fac6f","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:03:02.191Z","_requestId":"2a50dd388a364b15840cdcad9dcd8a24"}
