{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312042117a62dd3a651c84de0","session_id":"da6f98d4-7e33-4c58-9c42-a371874e10ea","message":{"id":"20260312042117a62dd3a651c84de0","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde8f9e9a049fbe4388fc42668916","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/REGISTRY.md","new_string":"### Verification\n\n- Code review: PASS\n- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n\n---\n\n## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n\n**Status:** completed\n**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n\n### Deliverables\n\n- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates pipeline status from multiple state sources\n- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with error extraction\n- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Heartbeat and error summary push to Telegram\n- `src/services/index.js` - Service exports for F-005 modules\n- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with heartbeat config options\n- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle event emitter\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated to use status-aggregator with --type parameter\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated to use log-pager with pagination support\n- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n\n### Acceptance Criteria Met\n\n- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status with --type parameter, progress stats, current feature info\n- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters\n- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto chunking with [N/M] segment numbering, --file option\n- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Configurable heartbeat with startup notification\n- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with execution time, log lines, silent mode\n- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted files\n\n### Config Options Added\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| HEARTBEAT_ENABLED | Enable/disable heartbeat |\n| HEARTBEAT_CHAT_ID | Target chat for notifications |\n| HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS | Heartbeat interval in milliseconds |\n| SILENT_MODE | Only push critical errors |\n| ERROR_LINES_COUNT | Number of error lines to include |\n\n### Key Decisions\n\n- D1: Independent status aggregator (keeps pipeline-controller single responsibility)\n- D2: Async message queue (push failures don't block main flow)\n- D3: Pagination via command-line parameters (simplified implementation)\n- D4: Timer-based heartbeat (simpler than event listening)\n- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no extra storage)\n- D6: Reuse existing message chunking from telegram.js\n\n### Verification\n\n- Code review: PASS\n- Unit tests: 60+ passing\n- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n- All acceptance criteria met","old_string":"### Verification\n\n- Code review: PASS\n- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n- Integration tests: 20+ passing"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":121905,"output_tokens":786,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_8d8fb4ee010f4820805a4013","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:21:31.330Z","_requestId":"2a50dd388a364b15840cdcad9dcd8a24"}
